parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Failure Leading to Engine Fire
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine failure can cause a vehicle to catch fire, resulting in serious injuries or fatalities, as well as significant property damage.
symptoms: The vehicle experiences engine trouble
smoke emerges from the engine

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: An oil filter adapter leak can cause oil to spill onto the engine and surrounding components, leading to engine damage, overheating, and potentially an engine fire.
symptoms: Oil leaks from the oil filter adapter
the vehicle requires frequent oil top-offs
the engine overheats
the vehicle experiences engine trouble.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rust failure of the seatbelt anchorage can cause the seatbelt to become inoperative, making it impossible to fasten the seatbelt, which can lead to increased risk of injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seatbelt mounting is rusted out
the entire belt pops out when trying to fasten
the seatbelt cannot be fastened
the seatbelt is loose and cannot be secured.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The jamming of the seatbelt buckle can prevent the seatbelt from being used, increasing the risk of injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seatbelt buckle is jammed into the seat handle recess
the seatbelt cannot be extracted
the seatbelt cannot be used
the seat cannot be raised or lowered.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The jamming of the seatbelt retractor can prevent the seatbelt from being used, increasing the risk of injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seatbelt retractor is jammed
the seatbelt cannot be fastened
the seatbelt cannot be released.
